column4: Factbox: U.S.  Canadian bids pour in for Amazon's second headquarters
column5: Dozens of U.S. and Canadian cities submitted proposals by the Oct. 19 deadline to host Amazon.com Inc's  second headquarters  which carries the promise of up to 50 000 high-paying jobs and $5 billion-plus worth of investment.

column4: Billions in tax breaks offered to Amazon for second headquarters
column5: Amazon.com Inc  is receiving offers of billions of dollars in tax breaks and other subsidies from cities and states across North America that are participating in a company contest to pick a location for its second headquarters. | Video

column4: Fox signed O'Reilly again knowing of new harassment settlement: report
column5: NEW YORK Bill O'Reilly  the Fox News commentator forced to resign in April  agreed to a $32 million sexual harassment settlement in January  and the network's parent knew about the deal when it gave him a new contract the next month  the New York Times reported on Saturday.

column4: Japan's Mitsubishi  U.S. partner to invest $1.8 billion in data centers: media
column5: TOKYO Japanese trading house Mitsubishi Corp  plans to set up a joint venture with U.S. data center operator Digital Realty Trust  and build around 10 data centers in Japan by 2022 for 200 billion yen ($1.8 billion)  the Nikkei said on Saturday.

column4: California judge tosses $417 million talc cancer verdict against Johnson & Johnson
column5: A California judge on Friday threw out a $417 million verdict against Johnson & Johnson  in a lawsuit by a woman who claimed she developed ovarian cancer after using its talc-based products like Johnson's Baby Powder for feminine hygiene.
